ZETIC: Build AI Apps That Run On-Device
(1st Place: $1000, 2nd Place: $600, 3rd Place: $400, All Winners: 3 Months of Melange Pro+ subscription and interview opportunities with ZETIC)

Overview
ZETIC builds an infrastructure for running AI on the edge devices which is fast, efficient, and private.
Melange is our dev tool that enables developers and builders to select, benchmark, and deploy AI models directly on the end-user’s smartphone within minutes, across CPU, GPU, and NPU.
In this challenge, you will build an AI-powered application using Melange (https://melange.zetic.ai/) to run AI models locally on real devices.
Your application must run its primary functionality on-device. Cloud inference may be used only for secondary tasks such as heavy computation or fallback.
What We’re Looking For
Strong submissions will:
Run core functionality directly on-device
Clearly separate on-device and cloud responsibilities
Optimize latency, efficiency, and resource usage
Deliver a working prototype with real-world usability
Must have used Melange SDK
What to Avoid
Avoid the following:
Cloud-heavy applications with minimal on-device usage
Simple wrappers around APIs without system-level thinking
Generic chatbots without meaningful functionality
Example Project Ideas
You can build applications across domains such as:
Healthcare
Education
Productivity
Accessibility
Some example directions:
On-device healthcare assistant that works offline with cloud fallback
Real-time transcription and summarization with local processing
Offline-first learning assistant for students
Accessibility tools using on-device speech or vision models
Smart assistant that runs core logic locally with optional cloud support
Technical Direction
You are encouraged to:
Use on-device models for latency-sensitive or privacy-critical tasks
Use cloud only for clearly secondary tasks such as heavy computation or fallback
Design clear separation between on-device and cloud responsibilities
Optimize for efficiency, responsiveness, and resource usage
Focus on building applications that run effectively on real devices.
Evaluation Criteria
Submissions will be evaluated based on:
Effective use of on-device inference with Melange SDK (primary functionality)
Clarity in separating on-device and cloud responsibilities
Performance, latency, and efficiency considerations
Overall user experience and usability
